	affiliations = {Shri Guru Gobind Singhji Institute of Engineering and Technology, Dept. of Electronics and Telecommunication Engineering, Nanded, India},
	abstract = {This paper introduces a scalable and cost-efficient AI framework for pharmaceutical business intelligence, pow-ered by fine-tuned LLaMA-2 models using Parameter-Efficient Fine-Tuning (PEFT) and Low-Rank Adaptation (LoRA). By updating only 0.39% of model parameters, the system reduces GPU memory usage, training time, and storage needs while maintaining performance. Deployed via a Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) pipeline linked to curated pharma datasets, the model supports domain-specific, context-aware decision-making. Applications include predicting patient responses in clinical trials, automating market intelligence from regulatory and financial documents, and optimizing supply chain operations through logistics forecasting. The framework incorporates data anonymization and differential privacy to ensure compliance and security. Experimental results show high accuracy in di-verse pharma tasks. To our knowledge, this is the first LoRA-augmented RAG system tailored for the pharmaceutical industry. Its modular design enables adoption by both large and mid-sized firms, offering a practical, low-infrastructure path to AI-driven insights and operational efficiency. © 2025 IEEE.},
