	abstract = {This paper addresses a critical limitation in the application of Large Language Models (LLMs) to enterprise environments: the inability to directly leverage proprietary structured data. While Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) frameworks have proven effective with unstructured data, a significant portion of organizational knowledge resides in dynamic, structured databases. We present a novel RAG pipeline designed to bridge this gap. Our method translates question into executable Structured Query Language (SQL) statements, retrieves real-time data from relational databases, and intelligently integrates this information with LLMs to generate outputs. This approach facilitates a dynamic and precise interaction with enterprise data while preserving the language understanding capabilities of LLMs. Experimental results demonstrate the effectiveness of our pipeline, achieving up to 8 7. 5% execution accuracy (EX) and 91.2% component matching (CM) accuracy in generating relevant and precise responses, which underscores its potential for advancing enterprise-level AI applications. © 2025 IEEE.},
