	affiliations = {ServiceNow, United States},
	abstract = {Agentic AI, powered by Large Language Models (LLMs), is revolutionizing how enterprises engineer and execute business processes. By advancing beyond generating situation-specific textual directives, Agentic AI enables "text-to-action," where natural language directives are translated into executable workflows autonomously. Despite these advancements, existing solutions often rely on coding concepts misaligned with business-focused directives, limiting accessibility and effectiveness of autonomous Agentic AI. This paper proposes a 2-step approach that combines no-code automation tools, such as Flow Designer, with Agentic AI-driven text-to-action capabilities. The capstone innovation, "text-to-flow," bridges the gap between business-focused textual directives and workflow execution, while ensuring operational robustness of the output workflow. Key contributions include tackling challenges such as directive granularity, context-awareness, generation latency, and evaluation complexity. Innovations introduced include intent pattern detection, Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) based object retrieval using hashtags, and UX strategies such as streaming previews and reasoning annotations. These advancements ensure workflows are executable, traceable, and explainable, while delivering a positive user experience despite the uncertainties and potential hallucinations of Generative AI. By introducing these innovations, our approach of text-to-flow addresses the limitations of existing Agentic AI text-to-action solutions, permitting a transformative path forward for enterprise autonomous business processing. © 2025 IISE Annual Conference and Expo 2025, Conference Proceedings. All rights reserved.},
