	affiliations = {Pradita University, Department of Information Technology, Jakarta, Indonesia; Nusa Putra University, School of Computer Science, Jakarta, Indonesia},
	abstract = {Business Intelligence plays a vital role in giving organizations the right and fast decision in today's data driven world. However, Business Intelligence (BI) faces significant challenges that slow down the decision-making process for business decision-makers (BDMs). This is necessary for the BDMs in order to establish the right systems that will facilitate business growth. There is structure that exists between BDMS and Information Technology (IT) in understanding and communicating data insight into business actionable strategies. On the other hand, many BI tools and technologies are often complicated and this hinders appropriate usage. In order to close this gap, this study investigates the possibilities of a multiagent Artificial Intelligence (AI)-powered BI framework that integrates Natural Language Processing (NLP) and RetrievalAugmented Generation (RAG). Using a modular architecture and specialized agents for data analysis, NLP, RAG, visualization, explanation, and recommendation, this framework fosters a cooperative effort that meets a range of user requirements and promotes a more user-friendly business intelligence experience. The framework offers the ability to close the gap between IT and BDMS by enabling BDMs to communicate with BI systems directly using natural language, acquire contextualized explanations, and receive tailored, actionable recommendations. A thorough assessment that combines quantitative and qualitative techniques shows how well the framework works to improve decision-making, automate intricate analysis, and enhance data exploration.  © 2025 IEEE.},
